### Version/Branch of Dear ImGui:

Version 1.92.2, Branch: docking 

### Back-ends:

imgui_impl_metal.mm + imgui_impl_metal.h

### Compiler, OS:

macOS + clang12

### Full config/build information:

_No response_

### Details:

Right now, the metal backend is only compatible up to Metal 3, Metal 4 includes **MTL4RenderPassDescriptor**, **MTL4CommandQueue**, **MTL4CommandBuffer** and **MTL4RenderCommandEncoder**. This means that upgrading your application (my game engine in this case) to Metal 4 will lead to compile errors due to incompatibility with the new MTL4 classes. This issue simply requests for overloaded functions for ImGui_ImplMetal_NewFrame and ImGui_ImplMetal_RenderDrawData to accept the new Metal 4 classes. 

Example Proposed Functions:

 ```objectivec
IMGUI_IMPL_API void ImGui_ImplMetal_NewFrame(MTL4RenderPassDescriptor* renderPassDescriptor);
IMGUI_IMPL_API void ImGui_ImplMetal_RenderDrawData(ImDrawData* drawData, id<MTL4CommandBuffer> commandBuffer, id<MTL4RenderCommandEncoder> commandEncoder);
```

Equivalent functions for metal-cpp bindings: 

```cpp
IMGUI_IMPL_API void ImGui_ImplMetal_NewFrame(MTL4::RenderPassDescriptor* renderPassDescriptor);
IMGUI_IMPL_API void ImGui_ImplMetal_RenderDrawData(ImDrawData* draw_data, MTL4::CommandBuffer* commandBuffer, MTL4::RenderCommandEncoder* commandEncoder);
```

